blog.name: queenofpanache
blog.title: ICE QUEEN
blog.description: Everything before the word 'but' is horse shit. - Jon Snow

body:
Lyanna Mormont & Ser Jorah Mormont

This thought just hit me this afternoon while I was at work.

So, we all know that Lyanna pledged to fight for the Starks (in BOTB) during the gathering in Winterfell. Now, judging by the situation, the pledge she made doesn’t seem temporary. Hence, I assume it’s a pledge of loyalty.

Now, assuming that Dany is the real antagonist in S8, I wonder how things are gonna be between Lyanna & Ser Jorah? Logically, Jorah was supposed to spy for Varys, but his thoughts & feelings changed along the way after spending his time as Dany’s queensguard. He seems to be loyal to her even after being exiled at one point of time.

Personally, IF the war was to happen between Dany & Starks, I think Jorah would be in a difficult position to choose between love & doing what’s right.

Just my two cents as I think it’s quite an interesting topic to discuss on. You’re welcome to agree to disagree. I’m open to opinions & your two cents.

blog.description: Jon/Dany/Bran/Arya Stan. Salty about the got ending. Also likes: The 100,  Star Wars, Stranger Things.

summary: Something I love about Dany and Jon is that we see people choosing to follow them not because of their inheritance but because...
body:
Something I love about Dany and Jon is that we see people choosing to follow them not because of their inheritance but because of their actions.

The Northerners choose Jon to be their King despite his bastard status because of his leadership qualities.

The Unsullied choose to follow Dany not because of her claim (does a westerosi claim mean something to them?) but because she’s the one who gave them back their freedom.

Jon and Dany are the King and Queen those people choose.

(and they are also the King and Queen Westeros need but that’s a post for another day).
